g.text: It does not cause zener shift
The gate of the JFET is held
at the positive supply of the zener.
The JFET will therefore conduct and
pull the negative leg of the zener down
until its source (the negative leg of
the zener) is about 2 V to 4 V below the
supply. It will then turn off and leakage
will be on the order of a few pA.
The 2k resistor is for protection only.
